        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer389636310" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1192448678242914860">The second book this year to make me bawl my eyes out (the first was Code Name Verity, by Elizabeth Wein). I&apos;ve never seen such a taboo topic like sibling incest handled in such a poignant and heartwrenching way. It&apos;s a testament to Ms. Suzuma&apos;s skill that I found myself desperately wishing for Maya and Lochan to be together. Simply amazing.</span>
  <span id="freeText1192448678242914860" style="display:none">The second book this year to make me bawl my eyes out (the first was Code Name Verity, by Elizabeth Wein). I've never seen such a taboo topic like sibling incest handled in such a poignant and heartwrenching way. It's a testament to Ms. Suzuma's skill that I found myself desperately wishing for Maya and Lochan to be together. Simply amazing.</span>
