<div id="review_4226425286" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4226425286" />
    <a title="♥️Dev♥️ ~ Dark &amp; Depraved Old Soul" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/126131750-dev-dark-depraved-old-soul"><img alt="♥️Dev♥️ ~ Dark &amp; Depraved Old Soul" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1633187726p2/126131750.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4226425286?book_show_action=true">Oct 13, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="♥️Dev♥️ ~ Dark &amp; Depraved Old Soul" class="user" itemprop="url" name="♥️Dev♥️ ~ Dark &amp; Depraved Old Soul" href="/user/show/126131750-dev-dark-depraved-old-soul">♥️Dev♥️ ~ Dark &amp; Depraved Old Soul</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/126131750-dev-dark-depraved-old-soul?shelf=5-stars">5-stars</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer4226425286&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4226425286" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12329352123722865999"><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1634179522i/32045653._SY540_.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i>“There are no laws, no boundaries, on feelings. We can love each other as much and as deeply as we want. No one, Maya, no one can ever take that away from us.”</i>
  </b>
</blockquote><br/><br/><b>5 &quot;Love You Forever. Lochie xx&quot; stars&quot;</b><br/><br/>Lochan, 17, strangely shy and rarely talks. Ever since his father left them high and dry and mom turned out as an alcoholic, he soon became responsible for his younger siblings. Making them three meals a day, doing others homework to earn money, save his mother when she ends up in jail, go </span>
  <span id="freeText12329352123722865999" style="display:none"><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1634179522i/32045653._SY540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i>“There are no laws, no boundaries, on feelings. We can love each other as much and as deeply as we want. No one, Maya, no one can ever take that away from us.”</i>
  </b>
</blockquote><br><br><b>5 "Love You Forever. Lochie xx" stars"</b><br><br>Lochan, 17, strangely shy and rarely talks. Ever since his father left them high and dry and mom turned out as an alcoholic, he soon became responsible for his younger siblings. Making them three meals a day, doing others homework to earn money, save his mother when she ends up in jail, go to his siblings' meetings and tournaments as their guardian, make sure they come home on time.........way too much responsibilities for a kid like him. He is still fighting his own demons, demons that consumed him after his father left and his mom start accusing him for looking and studying like his father. The only person who understand him, love him, care him, help him is his best friend, his soulmate, his sister.<br><br>Maya, 16, she has always been the one to help her brother and bear this burden with him. And now both of them are in love. But can a love like theirs survive?<br><br><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i>“You’ve always been my best friend, my soul mate, and now I’ve fallen in love with you, too. Why is that such a crime? I want to be able to hold you and kiss you and- and do all the things people in love are allowed to do. I want to spend the rest of my life with you.” “We will. We’ll find a way, Maya, we have to.”</i>
  </b>
</blockquote><br><br>So first of all, yea fellas I'm all kinds of fucked up but I don't care! I know <i>incest</i> is something that our society look down upon and most people is disgust/uncomfortable with the fact. even if it's a book. In real life do I recommend this type of love? No. But this is a book. In books everything is possible. Maybe that's why I read so much. Actually in these book the idea of "incest" or this "brother and sister falling in love" didn't disgust me as I thought.<br><br>Mind you, if you are thinking this is about teens being horny, and can't control themselves I COMPLETELY DISAGREE. These stories are not about kids who can't control their raging hormones. It's far from that. Believe me. <br><br>If it was all about sex, Loch could have raped his little sister too. If it was just about sex Lochie wouldn't have kill himself to set others free. If it was just about sex both of them would have run away. If it was just about sex, Maya could have actually accuse Loche.<br><br>A brother and a sister have a far more stronger connection than normal strangers.<br>I've seen many hating Maya saying she's the horny kid who killed her brother ................NO. She is not! If she didn't act up, Lochie would have gone through depression alone and might have killed himself because of all the suffering. With Maya, Lochie was free. I'm glad they got to be together one last time.<br><br><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i>Only with Maya can I really be myself. We share the burden together and she is always on my side, by my side. I don’t want to need her, to depend on her, but I do, I really do.</i>
  </b>
</blockquote><br><br>Both Maya and Lochie have gone through something, normal people wouldn't have survived. Father gone, mom a alcoholic-sex addict, looking after a brother with depression, and two little kids, one barely out of her wet drawers.....Maya and Lochie was the heart, the glue in their family. From a very young age both of them took heavy responsibilities that aren't meant for kids. In the end it cost half of their life, time, sleepless nights, friends and the world. They had no one in the world but yet they took care of the little ones, looked out for their depressed brother, soothed their mom (<b>YOU BLOODY BITCH! I KILLED YOU A 1000 TIMES IN MY MIND YOU WHORE!! If I was right infront of you I'll carve your children's name on your skin with a knife that's painted with a snake's venom, cut your half your head and your arms and legs and leave you to bleed for 3 days</b>). *Deep breath*<br><br> So in the midst of all that suffering, the pent up depression, the anxiety they found love and happiness in each other because no one else in the world can understand them the way they understood each other. They both know they can only depend on each other.<br><br>It's bittersweet because love like that is illegal. Lochie is the kind of brother every sibling need. A good friend, worries over is siblings, love them like his own, sacrifice his life to spare them, forgive them without limits. And the end, when Lochie killed himself to spare Maya and the kids, his last thoughts broke me. I'm happy that Maya didn't commit suicide too and stayed for the kids. But I get this tiny feeling she might have killed herself after the kids grew.<br><br>A heartbreaking, forbidden love story of a brother and sister !<br><br>💔💔<i>His last thoughts</i>:<br><br><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i>A harsh sob breaks the still air. And then I let go.<br><br>Willa’s big blue eyes, Willa’s dimpled-cheeked smile. Tiffin’s shaggy blond mane, Tiffin’s cheeky grin. Kit’s yells of excitement, Kit’s glow of pride. Maya’s face, Maya’s kisses, Maya’s love.<br><br>Maya, Maya, Maya . . .</i>
  </b>
</blockquote><br><br><u>Tropes</u><br><br>-Incest<br>-Shy hero/ Confident heroine<br><i>Note: No HEA, Carries violent themes such as suicide and more</i><br><br>HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!!!!!! Enjoy!!!<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1634180756i/32045673._SY540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><i>I'm so glad I found a picture of the bracelet, Lochie bought for Maya with all the money he saved!Damn I'm crying again!</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="12329352123722865999" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


